obo:ECO_0007719  a  owl:Class .

gomodel:SYNGO_1256  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Geerts et al study the distribution of tomosyn-2 in mouse hippocampal neurons by immunocytochemistry and live cell imaging. The data shows colocalization of tomosyn-2 with the SV/DCV marker VAMP2 and and the DCV marker chromogranin B (including quantification of the colocalization using Pearson's correlation and Manders overlap) in fixed neurons. Time-lapse imaging and corresponding kymographs show co-migration of tomosyn-2 with synapsin 1, suggesting indirectly their common association to synaptic vesicles, however this finding requires further evidence.. Experimental description: Neuronal cultures\n\nAnimals were housed, bred and experimentally used according to Institutional guidelines and Dutch and U.S. governmental laws with prior approval from the institutional animal research ethics committee (\"Dierexperimentencommissie Vrije Universiteit/VU medisch centrum\"; approval number FGA11-03), ensuring minimum discomfort of animals. All procedures were approved by the C57BL/6 wild type mice were obtained from Harlan (Horst, The Netherlands). Tom-1KO/KO and Syt-1KO/KO mice were described" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-1542-3498" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0808-7003" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-3898-5197" ;
        dc:date           "2018-05-31" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_CC_1256" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10090" .

